race.comment: OYSTER LANE (2) resumes and has impressed in much tougher Open 2 company in town. Missed a whisker at Caulfield on debut behind Sonofkirk and got even closer at Flemington following. He'll be naturally improved and placed his latest jumpout. John Allen rides and has been with him all along. ALPHABET (4) placed at Yarra Valley second-up and there was plenty of merit in the effort. Jumps from an inside gate today and has more to give. Stablemate THALESTRIS (10) resumes and has won both jumpouts. She had good support here on debut and looks to have improved with the time away. Draws to advantage and Ben Melham is a key jockey engagement. SUPERLIV (8) resumed in the ALPHABET race and just came up short racing forward. Jumps from the inside barrier and with extra fitness will get every chance.
